The paper deals with the construction of quadrilateral meshes for planar point sets, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of combinatorial techniques to derive upper and lower bounds, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of constructing quadrilateral meshes is related to graph theory, which could place the paper under cs.GR (Graph Theory). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their complexity, which could also make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
